metadata.name: Akuma ðŸ‘¹ #9
metadata.description:
ðŸ‘¹Akuma means Demon in Japanese. This series takes inspiration in manga and samourai movies, and are the direct descendents of my Codevember Walker and Titan series, featuring creative coding to give life and personality to "Walkers".

Each Akuma is part of an imaginary world and walks endlessly in their own way: elegant for fews, terrifying for others, peaceful for somes.. 

To re-enforced their personality and play with the concept of fx-hash I teamed-up with the musician & composer Faubourg to add a generative sound track, now each Akuma has his own track from around ~3200 possibilities and the solo-lead(10%) and solo-pad (1%) have their own visual universe, but I will not spoil you more ;)

ðŸŽ¶Note : You need to click to play the music and make your akuma heart beating .

Click once : Start the music and make your akuma heart beating 
Drag : Control the camera 
Pinch / mouse-wheel : Zoom
Enjoy!

Tw makio64
Faubourg : https://linktr.ee/faubourg

PS:The profit of this NFT will be shared with Faubourg

metadata.name: The Space Inside #63
metadata.description:
Points fill in shapes on a warped noise field. The resulting images range from soft water colors to distorted, pixelated CRT screens. 

The image is drawn at 3000x3000px and scaled to the browser size. 

Viewing in desktop Chrome is recommended for the best results.
Press â€™sâ€™ to save a screenshot. Image size is 3000x3000px
Press â€™pâ€™ to pause/resume.

Features:
- Two palette sets
- Light or dark background
- 70% color image, 30% monochrome
- Various combinations of circles and rectangles
- All rectangles 
- 7 types of shapes: random circles, packed circles, checkerboard, orbs, ring, spiral, checkerboard and orbs
- Rectangles snap to a grid
- Fuzzy lines connected groups of drawing points
- Fuzzy lines around the dots
- Bright border on the shapes

Rare
- 9% to have a soft monochrome and color palette

metadata.name: Pobbles #254
metadata.description:
The pobbles are generative blob-rocks: staring in silence, sometimes half-smiling, generally bored. 

â€¢ The pobbles are digital recreations of a series of rock-doodles by S.F.Kislev (my big brother). They are an attempt to capture a specific, singular handwriting, and evolve it using code. 
â€¢ See the original, 2014 handmade version here - https://pobbles.tez.page..
â€¢ Alternative titles considered include Pegglesâ„¢, Plopsâ„¢, Blobbiesâ„¢, Floofsâ„¢, Flintstonesâ„¢, Lardiesâ„¢, Plumpsâ„¢, Fatsâ„¢ and Wet-Onesâ„¢. 
â€¢ The pobbles are written entirely in paper.js and p5.js. 
â€¢ The pobbles are an effort to take generative art into the realm of the cute. 
â€¢ They work well with toddlers.
